Project description

TensorFlow is an open source software library for high performance numericalcomputation. Its flexible architecture allows easy deployment of computationacross a variety of platforms (CPUs, GPUs, TPUs), and from desktops to clustersof servers to mobile and edge devices.

Originally developed by researchers and engineers from the Google Brain teamwithin Google's AI organization, it comes with strong support for machinelearning and deep learning and the flexible numerical computation core is usedacross many other scientific domains. TensorFlow is licensed under Apache2.0.
